 book takes an incisive look at the importance of architecture and design on the spatial aspects of health and public health. Numerous successful Austrian projects—from health centers and care homes to results achieved through private initiatives—are provided as examples.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aArchitektur. 4aGesundheit. 4aGesundheitseinrichtungen. 4aGesundheitsinitiativen. 4aGesundheitszentren. 4aInitiativen. 4aNachbarschaft. 4aPflegeheime. 4aPublic Health. 4aRaumplanung. 4aVersorgungskonzepte. 4aÖsterreich. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aBenz, Lene, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLehner, Judith M. , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMaierhofer, Magdalena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchelling, Kathrin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTemmel, Evelyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cprintz978386859770740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978398612009240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783986120092423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783986120092/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK